on-end change-id="41600132-9cb6-47b6-a7c9-1194dcc65fef"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="7e7115d1-d470-40bb-fb29-0d9ad5d0937f" timestamp="1656533826988"?>equality;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-526ea180-b81c-41aa-ad0d-298055a34f75"><p>analyse gender inequality risks and gender equality possibilities when engaging with external stakeholders, take appropriate actions to avoid and/or mitigate risks, and to promote gender equality possibilities;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7e7115d1-d470-40bb-fb29-0d9ad5d0937f"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="d9938e5d-ea60-44c1-ccd9-a582e8d4d890" text="." timestamp="1671544001662"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="ca605279-2296-488c-a5f0-78ed4b286377" timestamp="1656533826988"?></p></list-item><list-item id="id-7e5ce758-07ae-4fb3-caca-40cdbd293049"><p>inform external stakeholders of its gender equality policy, strategies and/or other relevant documents that express commitment for gender equality and prevention of stereotypes, discrimination and sexual and gender-based violence;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-4548979d-63e8-4a9d-a002-67472e811621"><p>reflect organisational gender equality commitments also in contractual arrangements with external stakeholders as relevant;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-6cda339f-e6c2-4d5d-edb3-27362025a1c3"><p>in engagement with/investments into actors in a dependency situation to the organisation (such as local communities, supply chain actors), set-up grievance mechanism for external stakeholders to prevent/protect, detect and respond to gender-based violence in relation to the organizations operational work;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-8bf85f5f-a892-4ad9-c7be-6d058e6563e3"><p>communicate gender equality commitments and grievance mechanism, in a manner which reaches intended users;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-13036dfa-0ef4-4706-ea01-658d62bec9a7"><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ca605279-2296-488c-a5f0-78ed4b286377"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="006c8b51-0694-405f-b8a1-1d102ee5f3e3" text="—     " timestamp="1671544254016"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="9ab61b35-3c7c-443b-fe08-c9dc04e9bf54" timestamp="1656533826988"?>promote role models that go beyond gender stereotypes and expand traditional roles assigned to women and men ;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-0ea6b3e5-e408-480f-d30d-f11388c84a52"><p>discuss and raise awareness of all relevant external stakeholders (such as schools, higher education establishments, etc..) of the gender equality, diversity and inclusion in its professions and activities.</p></list-item></list><p/><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="9ab61b35-3c7c-443b-fe08-c9dc04e9bf54"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="2cb0977f-48f5-46eb-f110-0ca0d0a89206" text="inform external stakeholders of its gender equality policy" timestamp="1671544032085"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="2597b7c2-4f6c-4d5e-dc93-12fe725e6dd9" text=".the diversitydiversof the" timestamp="1670261039659"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="d14f1863-b251-4d34-c75a-d958ab06f6ff" text=" of women who work in professions and activities that are predominantly masculine, and role models of men who work in professions and activities that are predominantly feminine;" timestamp="1668784525621"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="a2bf86af-aa12-4119-cd0f-e87f8aea42bd" text=" " timestamp="1666857899620"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8763689" change-id="b195e6ac-9e04-4572-e3d4-9e9f43433910" text="or " timestamp="1656589962495"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="6c475294-5933-4a17-e1a3-93d06e857ed6" text="company" timestamp="1666857650073"?><p/></sec>